The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, June 06, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, June 6, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Chowringhee. Barricaded for flyover construction.				 																																	AJC Bose Road, in front of Calcutta Club and Rabindra Sadan. A flyover is coming up.				 																																	Southern Avenue. Construction on the drainage pumping station is in progress.				 																Club fest				 																																	Calcutta Club will stage Ekti Abastab Galpo, as part of the Inter-Club Drama Festival hosted by Outram Club, at Gyan Manch at 7 pm. Outram Club will enact Abasheshe at 8.15 pm.				 																Workshops				 																																	A workshop on Bengali music by Haimanti Shukla at Nehru Childrens Museum from 3 pm to 6 pm.				 																																	A workshop on Chhau dance of Saraikela, organised by Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, at Aikatan, Salt Lake, 10 am to 5 pm.				 																																	A summer workshop for youngsters on modern dance, theatre, creative expression and folk dance at Padatik.				 																Furniture				 																																	Furniture Show 2003 at Ice Skating Rink.				 																Photos				 																																	Landscapes, an exhibition of photographs by Soumitra Datta, at Academy of Fine Arts.				 																																	A photographic exhibition on the Medieval City of Gaur at State Archaeological Museum.				 																																	Bhavna, a display of photographs and paintings, at Academy of Fine Arts, North Gallery, 3 pm-8 pm.				 																Pottery				 																																	An exhibition of pottery at Central Cottage Industries Emporium.
